<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Bayern Munich midfielder Michael Cuisance is closing on an £18million move to Leeds United.</p>

<p>The Frenchman has been given permission to speak to Leeds after telling the European champions he wanted more game time.</p>

<p>The 21-year old playmaker cost Bayern £9m when he joined from Monchengladbach last year and has been watched by Newcastle United.</p>

<p>Midfielder Michael Cuisance has been given permission to speak with Leeds over £18m deal</p>

<p>Leeds are discussing a five year contract for the France U20 international.</p>

<p>Leeds also want a winger with Gyrano Kerk from Utrecht and Leicester City’s Demarai Gray on their wishlist.</p>

<p>Meanwhile, Bayern are considering a bid for Norwich City right-back Max Aarons after missing out on Ajax full-back Sergino Dest who is joining Barcelona.</p>

<p>Leeds are also keen to sign Leicester’s Demarai Gray (above) and Utrecht's Gyrano Kerk</p>
